---
import BaseHead from "../components/BaseHead.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import "../styles/global.css";
import { AUTHOR_NAME_FULL, AUTHOR_NAME, AUTHOR_EMAIL, SOCIALS } from "../consts.ts";
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead title="about" description="self-taught web developer from pakistan, building in public at devsafar." />
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="noise"></div>
    <Header />
    <main>
      <aside class="sys-info">
        <h2>./sys_specs</h2>
        <div class="spec-row">
          <span class="spec-key">usr:</span><span class="spec-val">{AUTHOR_NAME_FULL}</span>
        </div>
        <div class="spec-row">
          <span class="spec-key">alias:</span><span class="spec-val">devsafar</span>
        </div>
        <div class="spec-row">
          <span class="spec-key">loc:</span><span class="spec-val">pakistan</span>
        </div>
        <div class="spec-row">
          <span class="spec-key">os:</span><span class="spec-val">arch linux (btw)</span>
        </div>
        <div class="spec-row">
          <span class="spec-key">stack:</span><span class="spec-val">web_technologies</span>
        </div>
        <div class="spec-row">
          <span class="spec-key">status:</span><span class="spec-val">bridging_the_gap</span>
        </div>
        <div class="spec-row">
          <span class="spec-key">v:</span><span class="spec-val">0.1.0-alpha</span>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <section class="bio-section">
        <h1>cat about.md</h1>
        <p>
          i am a developer building out of pakistan. this space, <strong>devsafar</strong>, 
          is my digital notebook—a public ledger of everything i am learning, 
          breaking, and fixing in real-time.
        </p>

        <div class="block-quote">
          "seekhte seekhte sikhana." <br />
          (teaching while still learning.)
        </div>

        <p>
          for many pakistani students, the barrier to entry in tech isn't a lack of 
          talent, but a lack of relatable guidance. technical documentation often 
          feels like a brick wall. my goal is to turn those walls into stepping 
          stones. 
        </p>

        <p>
          <strong>devsafar</strong> is a portfolio project in itself—not a polished 
          showcase, but a raw documentation of the <em>safar</em> (journey). i write 
          about modern web technologies, open-source explorations, and the 
          lessons learned from managing a temperamental arch linux setup.
        </p>

        <p>
          if you are currently in your <code>init</code> phase, i hope these logs 
          help you compile your own path. we are all just figuring it out, one 
          <code>sudo</code> command at a time.
        </p>

        <div class="contact-cmds">
          <div class="cmd-line">
            <span>// drop an email:</span>
            <a href={`mailto:${AUTHOR_EMAIL}`}>ping --mail {AUTHOR_NAME}</a>
            <button class="copy-email-btn" data-email={AUTHOR_EMAIL}>[ copy ]</button>
          </div>
          <div class="cmd-line">
            <span>// connect on socials:</span>
            <a href={SOCIALS.github} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">github</a>
            <a href={SOCIALS.x} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">x</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>

<script>
  const copyBtn = document.querySelector('.copy-email-btn');
  if (copyBtn) {
    copyBtn.addEventListener('click', async () => {
      const email = copyBtn.getAttribute('data-email');
      if (email) {
        await navigator.clipboard.writeText(email);
        copyBtn.innerHTML = '[ copied! ]';
        setTimeout(() => { copyBtn.innerHTML = '[ copy ]'; }, 2000);
      }
    });
  }
</script>

<style>
  main {
    flex: 1;
    padding: 4rem 5vw;
    margin: 0 auto;
    max-width: 1150px;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 350px 1fr;
    gap: 4rem;
    width: 100%;
  }
  .sys-info {
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding: 2rem;
    height: fit-content;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.01);
  }
  .sys-info h2 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--neon);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  .spec-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 80px 1fr;
    margin-bottom: 0.8rem;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }
  .spec-key {
    color: var(--muted);
  }
  .spec-val {
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .bio-section h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3.5rem);
    font-family: "JetBrains Mono", monospace;
    font-weight: 800;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    text-transform: lowercase;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .bio-section h1::before {
    content: "> ";
    color: var(--neon);
  }
  .bio-section p {
    color: #aaa;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  .block-quote {
    border-left: 2px solid var(--neon);
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    margin: 3rem 0;
    font-style: italic;
    color: #888;
  }
  .contact-cmds {
    margin-top: 4rem;
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px dashed var(--border);
  }
  .cmd-line { font-size: 0.9rem; display: flex; align-items: center; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.5rem; }
  .copy-email-btn { background: none; border: none; color: var(--neon); cursor: pointer; font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.85rem; transition: opacity 0.2s; padding: 0; margin-left: 0.5rem; }
  .copy-email-btn:hover { opacity: 0.7; }
  .cmd-line span {
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-right: 1rem;
  }
  .cmd-line a {
    color: var(--text);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px dashed transparent;
    transition: border 0.2s;
    border-bottom-color: var(--neon);
  }
  @media (max-width: 800px) {
    main {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 3rem;
    }
  }
</style>
